44&newsid=2828 |title=Stranraer add McInnes |date=3 August 2009 |publisher=Scottish Football League |accessdate=22 November 2009}}{{Dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Alan Johnston]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n| [[Free transfer (football)|Free]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/st_mirren/8268799.stm|title=St Mirren tie up Johnston signing |date=22 September 2009|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jamie Adams]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]]\n||[[Loan (sports)|Loan]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/killie-ace-jamie-adams-checks-1040949|title=Killie ace Jamie Adams checks at Partick Thistle for two months |date=3 November 2009|publisher=Daily Record|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{noteslist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.kilmarnockfc.co.uk/ Kilmarnock F.C. website]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/k/kilmarnock/default.stm BBC My Club page]\n\n{{Kilmarnock F.C.}}\n{{Kilmarnock F.C. seasons}}\n{{2009\u201310 in Scottish football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2009-10 Kilmarnock F.C. season}}\n[[Category:Kilmarnock F.C. seasons]]\n[[Category:Scottish football clubs 2009\u201310 season|Kilmarnock]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n| club = [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]\n| season =[[2009\u201310 in Scottish football|2009\u201310]] \n| chairman =Michael Johnston\n| manager =[[Jim Jefferies (footballer)|Jim Jefferies]]<br><small>(until 11 January 2010)</small><br>[[Jimmy Calderwood|Jimmy Calderwood]]<br><small>(from 14 January)</small><br>\n| stadium =[[Rugby Park]]\n| league = [[2009\u201310 Scottish Premier League|Premier League]]\n| league result ='''Eleventh Place'''  \n| cup1 = [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]]\n| cup1 result ='''Quarter-Final''', lost to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] \n| cup2 = [[2009\u201310 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] \n| cup2 result ='''Third Round''', lost to [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n| league topscorer =<br />[[Kevin Kyle|Kevin Kyle]] (8)\n| season topscorer =<br />[[Kevin Kyle|Kevin Kyle]] (10)\n| highest attendance =10,662 v [[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]], 8 May 2010 <!--LEAGUE ONLY-->\n| lowest attendance  =4,068 v [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton]], 24 March 2010 <!--LEAGUE ONLY-->\n| average attendance =League: 5,919\n|  pattern_la1 =\n |  pattern_b1 =\n |  pattern_ra1 =\n |  pattern_sh1 =\n |  pattern_so1 =\n |  leftarm1 =\n |  body1 =\n |  rightarm1 =\n |  shorts1 =\n |  socks1 =\n |  pattern_la2 = \n |  pattern_b2 = \n |  pattern_ra2 = \n |  pattern_sh2 = \n |  pattern_so2 = \n |  leftarm2 = \n |  body2 = \n |  rightarm2 =\n |  shorts2 = \n |  socks2 = \n| prevseason = [[2008\u201309 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n| nextseason = [[2010\u201311 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2010\u201311]]\n}}\n\nThe [[2009\u201310 in Scottish football|2009\u201310 season]] was [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock's]] eleventh consecutive season in the [[2010\u201311 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]], having competed in it since its inauguration in [[1998\u201399 Scottish Premier League|1998\u201399]]. Kilmarnock also competed in the [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]] and the [[2009\u201310 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]].\n\n==Summary==\n\n===Season===\nKilmarnock finished eleventh in the [[2009\u201310 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]] with 33 points<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/table/_/league/SCO.1/season/2009/scottish-premiership | title=Scottish Premiership Table 2009-10 | publisher=[[ESPN FC]] | work=espnfc.com | accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>, only being spared from relegation on the final day of the season with a 0\u20130 draw against [[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/8666163.stm | title=Kilmarnock 0 - 0 Falkirk | publisher=[[BBC]] | work=BBC Sport | date=8 May 2010 | accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref> Kilmarnock also reached the third round of the [[2009\u201310 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], losing to [[St. Mirren F.C.|St. Mirren]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_cups/8266322.stm | title=Kilmarnock 1 St Mirren 2 | publisher=[[BBC]] | work=BBC Sport | date=22 September 2009 | accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref> and the quarter\u2013final of the [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup]], losing to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/8588252.stm | title=Celtic 3 Kilmarnock 1 | publisher=[[BBC]] | work=BBC Sport | date=27 March 2010 | accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n\n''Kilmarnock's score comes first''\n\n{{legend2|#ccffcc|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffffcc|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffcccc|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#cccccc|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main|2009\u201310 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Match\n! Date\n! Opponent\n! Venue\n! Result\n! Scorers\n! Attendance\n! Report\n|-bgcolor=#CCFFCC\n| 1\n| align=left|15 August 2009\n| align=left|[[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton]]\n| [[Rugby Park|H]]\n| 3\u20130\n| align=left|[[Kevin Kyle|Kyle]] 34', 52' [[Jamie Hamill|Hamill]] 68'\n| 5,307\n| [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/8200792.stm BBC Sport]\n|- bgcolor=#FFCCCC\n| 2\n| align=left|22 August 2009\n| align=left|[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]\n| [[Fir Park|A]]\n| 1\u20133\n| align=left|[[Jamie Hamill|Hamill]] 88'\n| 5,093\n| [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/8210733.stm BBC Sport]\n|- bgcolor=#FFCCCC\n| 3\n| align=left|29 August 2009\n| align=left|[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n| [[Rugby Park|H]]\n|